                <a href="contact.html" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900">Contact</a>
            </nav>
            <div class="md:hidden">
                <button class="text-gray-800 focus:outline-none">
                    <svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 6h16M4 12h16m-7 6h7"></path></svg>
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12">My Course Projects</h1>
        <div class="space-y-12">
            <!-- Project 1 -->
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Information Literacy Analysis</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">This project involved a deep dive into effective research strategies. I selected a topic and used three individual search engines and three meta-search engines to gather information. The core of the project was applying Boolean operators (`AND`, `OR`, `NOT`, `" "`) to create precise queries. I then evaluated the credibility of the websites I found using the CRAAP test (Currency, Relevance, Authority, Accuracy, Purpose), comparing high-quality academic sources against poorly designed commercial sites.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- Project 2 -->
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Website Design & Development Plan</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">For this project, I planned a complete website from the ground up. This involved creating a sitemap to outline the site's structure and developing detailed storyboards (wireframes) for the homepage and a secondary page. I made conscious design choices regarding layout, color scheme, typography, and navigation to ensure a professional and user-friendly experience, based on the principles from the Web Style Guide.</p>
            </div>
            <!-- Project 3 -->
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Academic Research Bibliography</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">This assignment focused on formal academic research. Using the GSU Library's databases (like PsycINFO and JSTOR) and Google Scholar, I located five peer-reviewed journal articles on a topic related to my major. The final step was to use Zotero, a reference management tool, to automatically format these sources into a bibliography using the APA 7th edition citation style.</p>
            </div>
             <!-- Project 4 -->
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Business Communication</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">This project involved professional writing. I learned the proper block format for a business letter and used a Microsoft Word template to create a formal job application letter addressed to a hiring manager at a major tech company. The focus was on professional tone, correct formatting, and clear communication.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="bg-gray-800 text-white py-8 mt-16">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center">
            <p>&copy; 2025 Alex | All Rights Reserved</p>
        </div>
    </footer>

</body>
